title: Lyft increases IPO range, expects to charge $70 to $72 a share
text: Lyft Inc. increased the amount it expects to charge for shares in its initial public offering Wednesday afternoon, raising the expected range to $70 to $72 a share.

title: The Lyft IPO: What You Need To Know
text: In the race to the U.S. markets, Lyft is about to lap Uber and other ride-hailing rivals.

title: US reportedly pushes Chinese owner of Grindr to divest the dating app
text: Chinese gaming company Beijing Kunlun Tech is seeking to sell Grindr after a U.S. government panel raised concerns about its ownership.

title: EU shuns US calls to ban Huawei from its future 5G networks
text: The European Union move comes despite U.S. pressure to boycott Huawei, citing fears of China using its equipment for espionage.
